 of a yagna
(sacrifice), he gave away all his wealth and other possessions.=


No one would, however, take the empire. So he invited the neighbouring Ki=
ng
who was an enemy and who was waiting for a suitable opportunity to snatc=
h it
away and gifted away the empire to him. The only thing that remained t=
o be
done was to leave the country.

He left at midnight in disguise, lay i=
n hiding during day time in other
countries so as not to be recognised and =
went about begging alms at night.
Ultimately he felt confident that his min=
d had matured sufficiently to be
free from egoism.

Then he decided to go t=
o his native place and there went out begging in all
the streets. As he was=
 not recognised by anybody, he went one day to the
palace itself. The watch=
man recognised him, made obeisance and informed the
then King about it, shi=
vering with fear.

The King came in a great hurry and requested him (Bhagir=
atha) to accept the
kingdom back,but Bhagiratha did not agree. =93Will you =
